To turn this mock-up into a colorful and interactive website, you can use HTML and JavaScript to create a dynamic and engaging user experience. Here's a brief outline of the steps you can take:

1. Create a basic HTML structure for the website, including the HTML tags for the head, body, and title.
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Joke Website</title>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="joke-container">
    <p id="joke">Funny Joke</p>
    <button id="reveal-punchline">Push to Reveal Punchline</button>
  </div>
  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
1. Create a JavaScript file (script.js) to handle the interaction between the user and the joke.
```javascript
const jokeContainer = document.getElementById("joke-container");
const joke = document.getElementById("joke");
const revealButton = document.getElementById("reveal-punchline");

revealButton.addEventListener("click", function() {
  jokeContainer.classList.add("reveal");
  setTimeout(function() {
    jokeContainer.classList.remove("reveal");
    joke.textContent = "Funny Joke";
  }, 1000);
});
```
1. Add CSS styles to the website to make it colorful and interactive.
```css
body {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

#joke-container {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  padding: 20px;
  text-align: center;
}

#joke {
  font-size: 24px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

#reveal-punchline {
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  border: none;
  color: white;
  font-size: 20px;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.reveal {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  padding: 20px;
}
```
With these steps, you can create a colorful and interactive website that allows users to push a button to reveal a real joke instead of a placeholder joke.
